
Additional space --> we dont' include space taken up by the input

we don't have control of what is outside the function, only inside.

public static void scare(int times) {
    for (int i = 0; i < times; i++) {
        sout("BOOOOO");
    }
}

scare(5) --> space complexity = O(1); --> only one variable "i"

public ArrayList<int> void testing(int times) {
    ArrayList<int> array = new ArrayList<>();

    for (int i = 0; i < times; i++) {
        array.add(i);
    }
    return array;
}

testing(5) --> O(n)


